text: Orexana is a genus of small, air-breathing land snails, terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Geomitridae. It is distributed along west coast of Morocco and Canary Islands. == Species == Species within the genus Orexana include: * Orexana ultima (Mousson, 1872) == References == Category:Stylommatophora Category:Stylommatophora stubs
